@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"
@TOC "Main"
If you have opened a lot of windows on your Workbench it is sometimes very
hard reaching the icons on the main Workbench window (Disks, AppIcons, etc.)
Many people use the "Backdrop" menu item to make the main Workbench window
a normal window (no backdrop) because this brings the Workbench window to
front. So one can easly access the icons and bring the Workbench window
back again later by selecting the "Backdrop" menu item once again. Un-
fortunately you have to activate one of the Workbench windows in order to
be able to activate the menu item (or use the keyboard shortcut). Often you
have to move windows, change their size or iconify them. This is over now!!

WBAttack is a little program which allows you to change the backdrop mode
of the main Workbench window. It is (mainly) intended to be used with pro-
grams like Toolmanager which allow starting programs with a configurable
hotkey. As such hotkeys can be used in any occasion (it does not matter
which window or screen is the active one) accessing the icons of the main
Workbench window will be very very easy. 
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements" "Requirements"
@TOC "Main"

WBAttack should work on any machine with at least @{FG SHINE}AmigaOS 2.0 (V36)@{FG TEXT}. I say
should because I don't know whether the "Backdrop" menu item is at the
same place in each version of the operating system. If on your Amiga it is
not the first item of the first Workbench-Menu then WBAttack will not work!!
If this is the case just contact me and I will release a more "compatible"
version of WBAttack.
@ENDNODE

